---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Mission"
  description="Ryzo is an Impact Franchise Studio. We meet young people where they live — in gaming, animated film, and digital stories — with fiercely entertaining work that sparks real change."
>

  <section class="mission-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow">Our Mission</span>
      <h1 class="display">
        Impact<br />
        <span class="accent-text">Franchise</span><br />
        Studio.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        We don't just tell stories. We build digital doorways that turn
        passive entertainment into personal agency.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who We Are -->
  <section class="section who-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="col-header">
          <span class="eyebrow">Who We Are</span>
          <h2 class="subheadline">A new kind<br />of studio.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-body">
          <p class="body-lg">
            Ryzo Studios is an Impact Franchise Studio. That means we
            aren't making content to fill a slot — we're building worlds
            designed to move young people from the inside out.
          </p>
          <p class="body-lg">
            We operate at the intersection of world-class entertainment
            and genuine purpose. Not one or the other. Both — at full
            intensity.
          </p>
          <p class="body-lg">
            Our founders come from Pixar Animation Studios. Our science
            partners are at Stanford and UCSF. Our audience is the next
            generation of people who will inherit a complicated world —
            and we believe they deserve stories that take them seriously.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Purpose -->
  <section class="section purpose-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="purpose-inner">
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Purpose</span>
        <h2 class="purpose-headline">
          Meet young people<br />where they live.
        </h2>
        <p class="purpose-body body-lg">
          Our audiences don't wait for a film to come to them.
          They're in Roblox at midnight. They're watching YouTube in the
          back of a car. They're scrolling before school. They live in a
          fractured, high-speed, deeply emotional world — and that's
          exactly where we show up, with fiercely entertaining stories
          that spark internal shifts and external activation.
        </p>
        <div class="purpose-platforms">
          {['Gaming', 'Animated Film', 'Digital Stories', 'Live Experiences'].map(p => (
            <span class="platform-chip">{p}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How We Do This — 3 Principles -->
  <section class="section how-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">How We Do This</span>
      <h2 class="subheadline">Three principles.<br />Every project.</h2>

      <div class="principles">

        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">01</div>
          <div class="principle-body">
            <h3 class="principle-title">We create franchises, not films.</h3>
            <p>
              We see the story through the same prism our audiences see
              their world. Roblox. YouTube. Netflix. YA novels. Merch.
              All of it is part of how they connect with, explore, and
              take action around a story and its core themes.
            </p>
            <p>
              "Release The Beast" isn't a film with a game attached.
              Rage Fighters isn't a game inspired by a film. They are
              two entry points into the same living world — designed to
              be experienced together, in any order, on any platform.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">02</div>
          <div class="principle-body">
            <h3 class="principle-title">We prize genuine entertainment.</h3>
            <p>
              We make things that young people connect to and want to
              play and watch — using all the tools of great storytelling.
              Character. Stakes. Emotion. Surprise. Beauty.
            </p>
            <p>
              Impact that doesn't entertain first isn't impact.
              It's homework. And kids can tell the difference.
              We don't make homework.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">03</div>
          <div class="principle-body">
            <h3 class="principle-title">We drive impact.</h3>
            <p>
              Our stories are designed to give the audience a way to
              transform themes into action in their lives. Not passive
              consumption — personal agency. Not awareness — activation.
            </p>
            <p>
              Every Ryzo franchise is built with a clear answer to the
              question: after experiencing this, what can a young person
              do differently? That answer shapes everything —
              the story, the game mechanics, the live events,
              the take-home resources.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Franchise Model -->
  <section class="section franchise-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="franchise-inner">
        <div class="franchise-text">
          <span class="eyebrow">The Model</span>
          <h2 class="subheadline">One world.<br />Every platform.</h2>
          <p class="body-lg">
            The Ryzo Franchise Model starts with a theme that matters —
            something young people are actually living through — and
            builds it out across every medium where they spend their time.
          </p>
          <p class="body-lg">
            The film makes them feel it. The game lets them practice it.
            The live events let them talk about it. The guides help the
            adults in their lives support it. And the merch lets them
            carry it with them.
          </p>
          <p class="body-lg">
            This isn't marketing. It's architecture.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="franchise-platforms">
          {[
            { medium: 'Animated Film', role: 'Feel it' },
            { medium: 'Roblox Game', role: 'Practice it' },
            { medium: 'Live Activations', role: 'Talk about it' },
            { medium: 'Educator Guides', role: 'Support it' },
            { medium: 'YA Novels', role: 'Go deeper' },
            { medium: 'Merchandise', role: 'Carry it' },
          ].map(({ medium, role }) => (
            <div class="franchise-item">
              <span class="franchise-medium">{medium}</span>
              <span class="franchise-role">{role}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research -->
  <section class="section research-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="research-inner">
        <span class="eyebrow">The Science</span>
        <h2 class="subheadline">Rigorous research.<br />Real outcomes.</h2>
        <p class="body-lg">
          Every Ryzo franchise is developed in active partnership with
          researchers at Stanford University and UCSF. Not as a
          validation exercise — as a creative constraint. The science
          shapes the story, the game mechanics, and the activation model.
        </p>
        <p class="body-lg">
          Because we don't want to move kids emotionally. We want to
          move them measurably.
        </p>
        <div class="research-partners">
          <div class="rp-card">
            <h3>Stanford University</h3>
            <p>Social-emotional learning, growth mindset, and educational psychology research shapes our curriculum and content design.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rp-card">
            <h3>UCSF</h3>
            <p>Child development and clinical research ensures our content is developmentally appropriate, trauma-informed, and clinically sound.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-sm cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-row">
        <h2 class="subheadline">Build with us.</h2>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/connect" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get in Touch</a>
          <a href="/supporters" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Our Supporters</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .mission-hero {
    min-height: 80vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding-block: 8rem 5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 70% 30%, rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.07) 0%, transparent 55%),
      linear-gradient(to right, #080316, #1c0832);
  }

  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-content .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .display { font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 8rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .accent-text { color: var(--accent); }

  .hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.375rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg-2);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  /* Shared background for all sections */
  .who-section,
  .purpose-section,
  .how-section,
  .franchise-section,
  .research-section,
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #080316 0%, #1c0832 100%);
  }

  /* Who */
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .col-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 7rem;
  }

  .col-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Purpose */
  .purpose-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .purpose-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .purpose-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.0;
  }

  .purpose-platforms {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .platform-chip {
    padding: 0.4em 1em;
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.3);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.06);
  }

  /* How */
  .how-section .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .how-section .subheadline { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }

  .principles {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .principle {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .principle:last-child { border-bottom: none; padding-bottom: 0; }
  .principle:first-child { padding-top: 0; }

  .principle-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .principle-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .principle-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .principle-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-2);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  /* Franchise */
  .franchise-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }

  .franchise-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .franchise-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .franchise-platforms {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .franchise-item {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .franchise-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .franchise-item:hover { background: rgba(245, 200, 66, 0.04); }

  .franchise-medium {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .franchise-role {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Research */
  .research-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .research-partners {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .rp-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .rp-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .rp-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-2);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cta-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .two-col, .franchise-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .col-header { position: static; }
    .principle { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
    .research-partners { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cta-row { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  }
</style>
